it.polimi.se2018.model

Class ToolCard

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.se2018.model.ToolCard
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ToolCard
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Class representing the Game's tool cards. Each card's effect is encoded in a placement rule and an HashMap that describes the effect's own state transitions.
    Author:
    Lorenzo Minto
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        Class constructor.
        Parameters:
        p - contains id, title, description, imageURL, neededtokens, tokensUsageMultiplier
        controllerStateRules - the state table that governs state transitions when the tool card is active.
        placementRule - the placement rules that need to be enforced when the tool card is active.
        possibleMovesCountSet - the number of possible dice moves
